        "en": "Generally speaking, compared to umbrellas left near urinals or washbasins (6651), those found inside private stalls (6753) should not be so easily forgotten. In fact, forgetting them is inherently difficult. This is because, unlike the brief actions of washing one's hands of using a urinal, a private stall usually requires one to hang multiple belongings such as bags or coats on a hook alongside the umbrella. Once finished, the natural sequence is to retrieve all items together before exiting: Given this logic, under what specific circumstances could an umbrella alone end up abandoned here?"
